				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">NEW BUG!<a name="15471"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 13 04 6:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You may have had this bug effect you or not, but here it is:
<br />

<br />
This new bug *poofs* mobs.  It happens when they are running away from your group.  So far I have noticed that root does prevent this.  I don't know exactly how it happens, but I do know that it helps to be right next to your mob when it is running away and have it snared/rooted. This bug happens to me MANY times while I kite.  The mob *poofs* and goes to what I believe to be the safe spot but it might not be.  I do know of where the spot is in TD only because I ran acrossed my *poofed* mobs while running back to the boats.  The mobs lose aggro and do not come back unless the spot they poof you is near you and you have a pet that is still on it.
<br />

<br />
This bug has been out for over a month and a half now and I have talked to GMs about it.  They have /bug it and I have /bug it, but still no patch to fix it.  If you know of this bug please /bug.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
