				<td colspan="2"><span>     I have had this happen to me many, many times. I have encountered it in the oldworld, Kunark, and Velious. It doesnt appear to matter if the mob is snared, rooted, or feared - it will still 'poof' away. 
<br />
     
<br />
I have also found that the mob may still 'poof' even if you meleed it before it began to run from low health. I have tested this in groups and soloing. It got to the point that I had 7 in a row 'poof' on me between Great Divide and Dreadlands. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />
<br />
     
<br />
What I have started to do is to leave track up as I engage and chant the mob down, so that if it 'poofs' I still have it on track. The times I have done this I have not been able to pick out a pattern of mob displacement. It appears to be totally random from my tests ( bad luck ). 
<br />
     
<br />
I've had mobs 'poof' on me in dungeons, outdoor zones, with groups, soloing, fear kiting, snare chanting, selos chanting, and swarm kiting. None retain aggro on me after they 'poof' and some don't even give xp even after I hunt them down again - yet the mob still leaves a corpse to be looted.
<br />
     
<br />
This bug is frustrating, and quite the ruiner of fun. I've /bug'd this and sent /feedback numerous times. I've not heard back at all from any GM or Guide, however.
<br />

<br />
Nothing we can do besides keep singing, eh? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
